20/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The EU has demanded that the Macedonian government return 1m euros worth of inappropriately spent EU funds, according to a report Saturday (18 October) in the ruling party's daily, <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I>.
According to the newspaper, the EuropeAid Co-operation Office sent a letter to the government suggesting part of the funds earmarked for rehabilitation from the Kosovo crisis was not utilised for legitimate purposes by the previous administration.
The EU has demanded an investigation.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 18/10/03)
